A department of Uruguay. Limita al norte con Durazno, al noreste con Treinta y Tres, al este con Lavalleja, al noroeste con Flores, al sur con Canelones (por el Paso Pache), y al suroeste con San Jose.
A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Melo. Limita al oeste con Durazno, al norte con Rivera y Tacuarembo, al este con Brasil, y al sur con el departamento de Treinta y Tres.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Paysandu. Limita al norte con el departamento de Salto, al sur con el departamento de Rio Negro, al este con el departamento de Tacuarembo y al oeste con el Rio Uruguay.
A department of southwestern Uruguay. Its capital is Colonia del Sacramento.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Durazno. Limita al norte con el departamento de Tacuarembo, al este con el de Cerro Largo, al sureste con el de Treinta y Tres, al sur con el de Florida, al suroeste con el de Flores y al noroeste con el de Rio Negro.

A department located to the south of Uruguay. Its capital is Canelones. Neighbouring departments are Maldonado and Lavalleja to the East, Flores to the North, San Jose to the West, and Montevideo to the South. Part of the southern border is formed by the Rio de la Plata.

A department of south-central Uruguay. Ubicado en el suroeste del territorio, limita al norte con el departamento de Rio Negro, al noreste con el de Durazno, al este con el de Florida, al sur con el de San Jose, y al oeste con el de Soriano, teniendo al suroeste un ligero contacto con Colonia.

A department located to the southeast of Uruguay. Its capital is Maldonado. Limita al norte con Lavalleja, al este con Rocha, al sur con el Rio de la Plata y el oceano Atlantico, y al oeste con Canelones.

A department of Uruguay. The capital is Minas. Limita al norte con el departamento de Treinta y Tres, al este con el de Rocha, al sur con los de Canelones y de Maldonado, y al oeste con el de Florida.

The northernmost department of Uruguay. Its capital is Artigas. Neighbouring departments are Salto to the South and Rivera to the Southeast. It limits to the East and North with Brazil, and to the West with Argentina. Portions of the department's border with Brazil are disputed.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Treinta y Tres. Ubicado en la zona oriental del territorio, limita al este con Brasil por tener costas sobre la Laguna Merin, y con los departamentos de Cerro Largo al norte, Durazno y Florida al oeste y Lavalleja y Rocha al sur.
A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Rivera. Limita al oeste con Salto, al norte y noreste con Brasil, al sureste con Cerro Largo y al sur con Tacuarembo.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is San Jose de Mayo. Limita al norte con Flores, al este con Florida, Canelones y Montevideo, al oeste con Colonia y Soriano (mediante una pequena interseccion), y al sur con el Rio de la Plata.
A department in the east of Uruguay. Limita al norte con Treinta y Tres, al este con Brasil, al sureste con el oceano Atlantico y al oeste con los departamentos de Lavalleja y de Maldonado.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Mercedes. Ubicado en el litoral oeste del territorio, limita al norte con el departamento de Rio Negro, al este con el de Flores, al sur con el de Colonia, y al oeste con la Republica Argentina, de la cual esta separado por el rio Uruguay.

The largest department of Uruguay. Its capital is Tacuarembo. Ubicado en la zona centro - norte del territorio, limita con los departamentos de Rivera, Salto, Paysandu, Rio Negro, Durazno y Cerro Largo.

A department of Uruguay. Its capital is Salto. Limita al norte con Artigas, al este con Rivera y Tacuarembo, al sur con Paysandu, y al oeste con la provincia argentina de Entre Rios, de la que lo separa el rio Uruguay.

A department of Uruguay located in the west of the country. Neighbouring departments are Paysandu to the North, Tacuarembo to the East, Durazno to the Southeast, and Soriano to the South. To the West is Argentina, from which the department is separated by the Uruguay River.
The capital of Maldonado Department of Uruguay.
The second city of Uruguay.
The capital city of Rocha Department, Uruguay.
A populated place. A town in Uruguay. It is located in western Uruguay, close to the border with Argentina, and about 160 km due north of Buenos Aires.
A populated place. A city in southwestern Uruguay, by the Rio de la Plata, facing Buenos Aires, Argentina.
A populated place. A city in Uruguay in the Rocha Department.
A populated place. A town in Uruguay. It is located in the department of Soriano, on the banks of the Rio Negro (Uruguay).

A populated place. A city in the province of Entre Rios, Argentina, on the left bank of the Gualeguaychu River (a tributary of the Uruguay River). It is located on the south-east of the province, approximately 190 km (120 miles) north-west of Buenos Aires.
Not Uruguay.

A populated place. A city in the south-east of the province of Corrientes in the Argentine Mesopotamia. It lies on the west bank of the Uruguay River, opposite Bella Union, Uruguay, about 440 km east-southeast of the provincial capital (Corrientes) and 640 km north of Buenos Aires.
Not Uruguay.
The second largest city in Uruguay.
Un termal ubicado en el Departamento de Salto, zona noroeste de Uruguay.
A populated place.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Southwestern, located in the west and southwestern part of the country, borders Albania to the west. Internally, it borders Pelagonia, Polog, Skopje, and Vardar statistical regions.
One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Northeastern, located in the northeastern part of the country, borders Serbia and Bulgaria.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Vardar, located in the central part of Macedonia, borders Greece to the south. Internally, it borders Pelagonia, Southwestern, Skopje, Southeastern, and Eastern.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Southeastern, located in the southeastern part of the country, borders Greece and Bulgaria. Internally, it borders Vardar and Eastern statistical regions.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Pelagonia statistical region is located in southwestern part of the Republic of Macedonia. It borders Greece and Albania. Internally, it borders Southwestern and Vardar statistical regions.
One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Polog, located in the northwestern part of the country, borders Albania and Kosovo. Internally, it borders Southwestern and Skopje statistical regions.

One of eight arbitrary statistical regions in the Republic of Macedonia. Skopje, located in northern Macedonia, borders Serbia to the north. Internally, it borders Vardar, Polog, Northeastern, Eastern, and Southwestern statistical regions.
A populated place. A village in the Republic of Macedonia, located 12 km south of the city of Ohrid. It is a popular beachside town along Lake Ohrid and lies at the foot of Galicica National Park.
A populated place.
Not Macedonia.
